<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="115" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Diagnostic description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="115">
Overall dark brown. Pronotal disc (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Costalampys bisbinotata (Pic) comb. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Female habitus, dorsal view; D, Female habitus, ventral view; E, Male antena, lateral view; F, Male pronotum, dorsal view; G, Male terminal segments, ventral view; H, Pygidium, dorsal view; I, Syntergite, dorsal view; J, Sternum IX, Ventral view; K, Aedeagus, dorsal view; L, Aedeagus, lateral view; M, Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-D); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (E; G); Scale bar: 0.5 mm (F; H-M)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543210" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">7F</figureCitation>
) dark brown, lacking vittae, pronotal expansions variable, from having anterior small vittae to almost entirely pale yellow, except by posterior margin, which is outlined in brown, blending with the dark brown disc color. Elytron (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Costalampys bisbinotata (Pic) comb. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Female habitus, dorsal view; D, Female habitus, ventral view; E, Male antena, lateral view; F, Male pronotum, dorsal view; G, Male terminal segments, ventral view; H, Pygidium, dorsal view; I, Syntergite, dorsal view; J, Sternum IX, Ventral view; K, Aedeagus, dorsal view; L, Aedeagus, lateral view; M, Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-D); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (E; G); Scale bar: 0.5 mm (F; H-M)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543210" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">7A, C</figureCitation>
) dark brown or brown, with a pale-yellow longitudinal stripe about 1/2 as long as elytra, usually with a roundish pale yellow spot at posterior 3/4 of elytral length, reaching inner suture, as wide as about 1/3
<normalizedToken originalValue="Ã—">x</normalizedToken>
elytral width. Legs (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Costalampys bisbinotata (Pic) comb. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Female habitus, dorsal view; D, Female habitus, ventral view; E, Male antena, lateral view; F, Male pronotum, dorsal view; G, Male terminal segments, ventral view; H, Pygidium, dorsal view; I, Syntergite, dorsal view; J, Sternum IX, Ventral view; K, Aedeagus, dorsal view; L, Aedeagus, lateral view; M, Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-D); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (E; G); Scale bar: 0.5 mm (F; H-M)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543210" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">7B, D</figureCitation>
) dark brown, except for trochanters and, sometimes, metacoxa, which are light brown. Sternum VIII with lateral vitreous spots. Pygidium (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Costalampys bisbinotata (Pic) comb. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Female habitus, dorsal view; D, Female habitus, ventral view; E, Male antena, lateral view; F, Male pronotum, dorsal view; G, Male terminal segments, ventral view; H, Pygidium, dorsal view; I, Syntergite, dorsal view; J, Sternum IX, Ventral view; K, Aedeagus, dorsal view; L, Aedeagus, lateral view; M, Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-D); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (E; G); Scale bar: 0.5 mm (F; H-M)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543210" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">7H</figureCitation>
) with medial 1/5 brown, with lateral pale-yellow stripes in males, entirely brown in females.
</paragraph>
<caption doi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543210" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" start="Figure 7" startId="F7">
