<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="115">
Pronotum (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Costalampys bisbinotata (Pic) comb. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Female habitus, dorsal view; D, Female habitus, ventral view; E, Male antena, lateral view; F, Male pronotum, dorsal view; G, Male terminal segments, ventral view; H, Pygidium, dorsal view; I, Syntergite, dorsal view; J, Sternum IX, Ventral view; K, Aedeagus, dorsal view; L, Aedeagus, lateral view; M, Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-D); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (E; G); Scale bar: 0.5 mm (F; H-M)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543210" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">7F</figureCitation>
) with sides rounded, divergent posteriorly. 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Male.</emphasis>
Total length = 7.8 mm; Pronotal length = 1.9 mm; Pronotal width = 2.8 mm; Elytral length = 6.2; Elytral width = 2.0 mm. Antennomere III (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Costalampys bisbinotata (Pic) comb. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Female habitus, dorsal view; D, Female habitus, ventral view; E, Male antena, lateral view; F, Male pronotum, dorsal view; G, Male terminal segments, ventral view; H, Pygidium, dorsal view; I, Syntergite, dorsal view; J, Sternum IX, Ventral view; K, Aedeagus, dorsal view; L, Aedeagus, lateral view; M, Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-D); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (E; G); Scale bar: 0.5 mm (F; H-M)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543210" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">7E</figureCitation>
) with lamella about 2
<normalizedToken originalValue="Ã—">x</normalizedToken>
longer than core antennomere. Sternum VI (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Costalampys bisbinotata (Pic) comb. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Female habitus, dorsal view; D, Female habitus, ventral view; E, Male antena, lateral view; F, Male pronotum, dorsal view; G, Male terminal segments, ventral view; H, Pygidium, dorsal view; I, Syntergite, dorsal view; J, Sternum IX, Ventral view; K, Aedeagus, dorsal view; L, Aedeagus, lateral view; M, Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-D); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (E; G); Scale bar: 0.5 mm (F; H-M)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543210" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">7G</figureCitation>
) with lantern of moderate size, occupying the medial 1.4 of the sternum, reaching its anterior margin. Sternum VIII with posterior margin bisinuose. Pygidium (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Costalampys bisbinotata (Pic) comb. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Female habitus, dorsal view; D, Female habitus, ventral view; E, Male antena, lateral view; F, Male pronotum, dorsal view; G, Male terminal segments, ventral view; H, Pygidium, dorsal view; I, Syntergite, dorsal view; J, Sternum IX, Ventral view; K, Aedeagus, dorsal view; L, Aedeagus, lateral view; M, Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-D); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (E; G); Scale bar: 0.5 mm (F; H-M)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543210" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">7H</figureCitation>
) with sides rounded, posterior corners weakly developed, posterior margin variably rounded to almost straight. Syntergite (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Costalampys bisbinotata (Pic) comb. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Female habitus, dorsal view; D, Female habitus, ventral view; E, Male antena, lateral view; F, Male pronotum, dorsal view; G, Male terminal segments, ventral view; H, Pygidium, dorsal view; I, Syntergite, dorsal view; J, Sternum IX, Ventral view; K, Aedeagus, dorsal view; L, Aedeagus, lateral view; M, Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-D); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (E; G); Scale bar: 0.5 mm (F; H-M)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543210" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">7I, J</figureCitation>
) with anterior margin mildly curved. Phallus (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Costalampys bisbinotata (Pic) comb. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Female habitus, dorsal view; D, Female habitus, ventral view; E, Male antena, lateral view; F, Male pronotum, dorsal view; G, Male terminal segments, ventral view; H, Pygidium, dorsal view; I, Syntergite, dorsal view; J, Sternum IX, Ventral view; K, Aedeagus, dorsal view; L, Aedeagus, lateral view; M, Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-D); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (E; G); Scale bar: 0.5 mm (F; H-M)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543210" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">7K-M</figureCitation>
) with dorsal plate almost straight in lateral view, with sides straight and acuminate at apical half. Paramere apex curved ventrally, ventral projection (lateral view) inconspicuous. 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Female.</emphasis>
Total length = 8.0-8.7 mm (aver. 8.35 mm); Pronotal length = 1.8-2.1 mm (aver. 1.95 mm); Pronotal width = 2.6-3.0 mm (aver. 2.8 mm); Elytral length = 6.3-6.7 mm (aver. 6.5 mm); Elytral width = 1.9-2.0 mm (aver. 1.95 mm). Antennomeres III-X with apical corners projected, pointed, sterna VI and VII lacking lanterns.
</paragraph>
